OL,6,F"Mark is now in a job at the trust
OL,7,Fwhere he's greatly valued by his team,
OL,8,Fand it's clear that he's thoroughly
OL,9,Fenjoying his new role. Mark's an
OL,10,Famazing ambassador for our trust, and
OL,11,Fan inspiration to everyone he meets."
OL,13,FAdjustments for Mark and Nathan were
OL,14,Fmade by his employer with new larger
OL,15,Fkeyboards and monitors, a rest area
OL,16,Ffor Nathan, and flexible rotas to make
OL,17,Fhis travel easier.
